    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/2059a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-03T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4911. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>, War Trade
                    Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 171. <persName>Stetson</persName>. Following resolution adopted War Trade
                    Board on recommendation Bureau War Trade Intelligence: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi> that War Trade Board approve in
                            principle creation of enemy trading list for Switzerland, provided same
                            shall be applied in manner not inconsistent with terms of agreement of
                            December 5, 1917, between War Trade Board and Government of Switzerland
                            relative to distribution in accordance with regulations of Société
                            Suisse de Surveillance Economique.<note n="1" xml:id="d146fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1917Supp02v02#pg_1185">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, Supplement 2,
                                    vol. II, pp. 1185</ref>–<ref target="frus1917Supp02v02#pg_1196"
                                    >1196</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Further resolved</hi> that no such list shall be
                            actually published or made effective until approval of War Trade Board
                            representative at Berne has been secured.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Will you cooperate with your colleagues in preparation of this list, communicate
                    text of resolution to War Trade Board representative, Berne, keep him advised of
                    progress in compiling list, when list is prepared ask that his approval be
                    telegraphed Washington for publication same? <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FPj1">Fuller</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
